<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare,Products.Contributor,Products.Analyzer" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="8" MadCap:lastHeight="675" MadCap:lastWidth="1133">
    <head>
        <link href="" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <ol type="1" class="Decimal">
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../Topics/OpenContentFileDocument.flsnp" />
            </li>
            <li>Place your cursor inside the table.</li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <MadCap:snippetText src="../StepsGeneral/DoOneOfTheFollowingDependingOnUI.flsnp" />
                </p>
                <ul type="1" class="FirstLevel">
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Ribbon </span>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../UIElements/SelectTableRibbon.flsnp" /> In the <span class="Emphasis">Data</span> section, select the <span class="Emphasis">Ascending</span> down arrow and then choose <span class="Emphasis">Advanced Sorting Options</span>.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Right-Click</span>&#160;<MadCap:snippetText src="../StepsGeneral/DoOneOfTheFollowing.flsnp" /><ul type="1" class="SecondLevel"><li><p>Right-click inside the table and from the context menu, select <span class="Emphasis">Sort Rows&gt;Advanced Sorting Options</span>.</p><p>OR</p></li><li>Right-click one of the appropriate tag bars to the left of the table, depending on the rows you want to sort (e.g., <span class="Emphasis">table</span>, <span class="Emphasis">thead</span>, <span class="Emphasis">tfoot</span>), and from the context menu, select <span class="Emphasis">Sort Rows&gt;Advanced Sorting Options</span>.</li></ul></li>
                </ul>
                <p>The Advanced Sorting Options dialog opens.</p>
            </li>
            <li>Click <img src="../../Images/new_item3_btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" />. A row is added to the grid on the right.</li>
            <li>In the <span class="Emphasis">Column</span> cell, click the down arrow and choose the column to sort by. Then in the <span class="Emphasis">Direction</span> cell choose <span class="Emphasis">ascending</span> or <span class="Emphasis">descending</span>.</li>
            <li>(Optional) If you want to add another row, telling <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> which column to sort by next, click <img src="../../Images/new_item3_btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> again. In the <span class="Emphasis">Column</span> cell, click the down arrow and choose the column to sort by next. Then in the <span class="Emphasis">Direction</span> cell choose <span class="Emphasis">ascending</span> or <span class="Emphasis">descending</span>. Repeat this for each additional row you want to add to the grid.</li>
            <li>(Optional) Use the buttons on the right side of the dialog if you want to remove or rearrange the order of any of the rows in the grid.</li>
            <li>(Optional) If you want <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> to automatically update the table sorting when you generate output, select <span class="Emphasis">Apply at compile time</span>. This can be useful in case you make changes to the table in the XML Editor and want <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> to automatically make the changes so you don't have to.</li>
            <li>(Optional) If you want <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> to apply the sorting rules to the table right away in the XML Editor, click <span class="Emphasis">Apply now</span>.</li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../StepsGeneral/ClickOK.flsnp" />
            </li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../StepsGeneral/SaveYourWork.flsnp" />
            </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>